<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The prefix SUPER- means "above" or "beyond" and creates over 200 valid Scrabble words. With a built-in 7-point base from S(1)+U(1)+P(3)+E(1)+R(1), SUPER- words carry serious scoring potential — making this one of the highest-value common prefixes in the game.</p>

<p>Unlike common prefixes like RE- (2pts) or UN- (3pts), SUPER- delivers more than triple the base value. Players who learn to spot SUPER- bingo opportunities gain a consistent edge, especially in mid-game when longer words open up premium squares.</p>

