<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategic Tips</h2>

<p>Mastering SUPER- is about knowing when to extend versus when to hold. These three tactics will help you capitalise on the 7-point base.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">P Value Advantage:</span> P(3) gives SUPER- a 7-point base — one of the highest prefix bases in Scrabble. Compare to RE- (2pts) or UN- (3pts). You start with a scoring lead before adding your suffix.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo Potential:</span> SUPER is 5 letters, so you need only 2 more tiles for a bingo (+50 bonus). SUPER+B = SUPERB (60pts with bonus). Hold SUPER and fish for high-value singles like B, J, K, or X.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Through-Tile Play:</span> Use existing letters on the board. If a C or K is already placed, play SUPER through it for SUPERCHICK or SUPERWEEK. This technique avoids burning extra tiles from your rack.</p>
  </div>
</div>

